Please add an email subscription feature for any issue events in a particular component (including creation of an issue and resolution/closure of an issue).

Right now you only get notification emails if you are watching a particular issue or you're the original poster or you're the assignee. This requires you to opt in to watching an issue. With a flurry of issues going along, unless you check JIRA regularly for new ones (which is an unreasonable expectation), you don't find out about them.

It should be possible to be notified of any new issues or changes in issue status in a particular component. The notification email should include a convenience link e.g. "Watch this issue" if it is something of importance.

In Jira 4.1.2, several comment boxes that start out small are resized when the user enters enough text so that the initial size of the comment box becomes too small. Often this resize operation puts my text cursor at the end of the comment box.

This is especially annoying if the comment box grows while I was editing in the middle of a comment, as it causes the remaining part of the sentence to appear at the end of the comment. The effect would be somewhat like this (I have put a (?) in the spot where the resizing happens, and a (!) where the cursor jumps to):

