JIRA currently limits the "Create vs Resolved Issues Report" to 300 day for daily reporting. This is too short. Many of our new product projects are in development for a year or more. In order to show "open" issues vs. time, need to gather data since the first bug was entered in a particular project. This is 354 days for "X" JIRA project. I would like to compare daily open trend with "Y", I need to view 1204 days.

As a work around, I could view weekly data but I don't see why can't select more than 300 days in report. I should be able to enter a arbitrary number which is only limited by the number of days to the earliest bug in the project.

