We have quite a few accounts which are used for batch processes, like accessing FishEye/Crucible data from JAC and vice-versa. If anyone tries to log in as that user incorrectly, the account becomes useless for the batch process because it requires a CAPTCHA to be completed.

We need a way to mark accounts which are used for batch processes (and have very secure passwords) as not requiring the additional CAPTCHA protection.

Discovered as part of this ADM issue (Atlassian-only): https://extranet.atlassian.com/jira/browse/ADM-8899

